      "creatureType": "",
      "blurb": "",
      "publicNotes": "<h3>Conversion notes (this module)</h3><p><strong>Role (A18):</strong> a Thassilonian-pattern <strong>sacrificial construct</strong> — a floating statue-engine fed by a soul nailed to its frame (the creation formulas are in Togomor's spellbooks, A44). This one bears the corpse of <strong>Ishani Dhatri</strong>, the Abadaran priest of Cressida's task #4, betrayed in the chapel (A13) by his own sister @UUID[Compendium.cotct-pf2e-conversion.cotct-actors.Actor.ch6VavanaDhatri1]{Vavana}. It stands inert against A18's southwest wall until the room is entered; the dead priest screams as it wakes. Destroy it, raise Ishani, and he relates the betrayal — and the castle's key secret: <strong>the apparent queen is a magical fake</strong>, and the real Ileosa is away at a 'place of great power.'</p>",
      "privateNotes": ""
    },
